article.headline: Tennessee Tech 16, VMI 10
article.story:
LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Brandon Shelby returned an interception 15
yards for a touchdown to lead Tennessee Tech to a 16-10 victory
over VMI on Saturday.

Shelby picked off Josh Lyles' pass in the fourth quarter to put
the Golden Eagles (2-1) ahead 16-3. Gary Price scored on a 24-yard
pass later in the quarter for VMI (0-3).

The Golden Eagles scored on a 1-yard run by Derek White in the
opening minutes in the first quarter. After a scoreless second
quarter, VMI's Grant Harris recovered a blocked punt to set up
Barrett Way's 32-yard field goal. The Golden Eagles responded with
a 24-yard field goal in the closing seconds of the third quarter.

Tennesee Tech gained 404 yards, compared to 274 for VMI.
